column4: Simple mean bound rate is the unweighted average of all the lines in the tariff schedule in which bound rates have been set. column5: Share of tariff lines with international peaks is the share of lines in the tariff schedule with tariff rates that exceed 15 percent. column6: Simple mean most favored nation tariff rate is the unweighted average of most favored nation rates for all products subject to tariffs calculated for all traded goods. column7: Simple mean applied tariff is the unweighted average of effectively applied rates for all products subject to tariffs calculated for all traded goods. Effectively applied tariff rates at the six- and eight-digit product level are averaged for products in each commodity group.
